als and objectives, and periodically review performance vs objectives.</p><p>Present technical update materials for internal reviews and to customers as needed.</p><p>Collaborate with Senior Director EPI and Common Engineering to evaluate emerging technologies and develop technical solutions to support innovation and new product initiatives.</p><p>Make recommendations to improve processes and project management of engineering.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Educational Requirements:</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>BS Degree in mechanical engineering or related degree required. MS or PhD degree in mechanical engineering or related degree preferred.</p><p>10 years of experience in semiconductor capital equipment, specifically engineering, design, and development of complex mechanical systems including: reactors, vacuum chambers, gas delivery systems, pneumatics, water cooling circuits, and vacuum systems required.</p><p>Minimum five years management experience in a technical or engineering supervisory role required.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Job Complexities</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Performs self-inspection of all work, and is responsible for ensuring that all work performed adheres to documentation requirements, company policies and procedures.</p><p>May be exposed to following hazardous materials used or exposed to hazardous environments while performing duties: loud noises, moving objects, flammable/toxic/corrosive materials, hot surfaces, lasers, infrared radiation, electrical/pneumatic (pressurized) circuits and adhesives. This will require that employee wear eye, hearing and hand protection as needed to be protected from exposure.</p><p>This position will require the use of cleanroom apparel and safety equipment. This work normally requires extended periods of standing and occasional lifting of up to 50 pounds.</p><p>.</p><p>Functional Knowledge &amp; Skills</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Business Expertise</p><p>Semiconductor capital equipment experience is required.</p><p>Knowledgeable in the requirements for CE, NFPA, Semi S2-95 and other relevant standards as applicable to semiconductor manufacturing equipment.</p><p>Deposition product knowledge required.</p><p>Understanding of materials: metals, plastics, surface coatings and surface finishes.</p><p>Computer background in Microsoft applications, Pro/ENGINEER and AutoCAD.</p><p>Knowledge of Design and Drafting best practices, ANSI Y14.5</p><p>Experience with ECO software and interfacing with manufacturing to release designs to production.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Collaboration</p><p>Has knowledge of best practices and how own area integrates with others; recommends product and process improvements.</p><p>Able to work/manage with a diverse team to achieve requirements and specifications on complex projects.</p><p>Ability to learn new skills quickly with minimal guidance.</p><p>A critical thinker with proven ability to create effective solutions to complex engineering problems.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Interpersonal</p><p>Excellent verbal and written communication; ability to present design concepts to management and peers in a professional and effective manner.</p><p>Ability to work in a team environment with aggressive deadlines and multiple priorities while maintaining a team player attitude.</p><p>Self-confident yet humble, with a high degree of integrity.</p><p>An intense desire for success, with an ability to learn and improve from past mistakes</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Technical/People Management</p><p>Strong technical management skills</p><p>Strong team motivation and leadership skills</p><p>Proven ability to drive projects and programs to closure</p><p>Ability to manage many simultaneous small projects in a fast-paced environment</p><p>Strong people management skills, ability to motivate and resolve conflict effectively</p><p>Strong project management skills</p><p>Ability to influence others to achieve common goal</p><